Usage: gem open GEMNAME [-e EDITOR] [options]

  Options:
    -e, --editor EDITOR              Opens gem sources in EDITOR
    -v, --version VERSION            Opens specific gem version


  Common Options:
    -h, --help                       Get help on this command
    -V, --[no-]verbose               Set the verbose level of output
    -q, --quiet                      Silence command progress meter
        --silent                     Silence RubyGems output
        --config-file FILE           Use this config file instead of default
        --backtrace                  Show stack backtrace on errors
        --debug                      Turn on Ruby debugging
        --norc                       Avoid loading any .gemrc file


  Arguments:
    GEMNAME     name of gem to open in editor

  Summary:
    Open gem sources in editor

  Description:
            The open command opens gem in editor and changes current path
            to gem's source directory. Editor can be specified with -e option,
            otherwise rubygems will look for editor in $EDITOR, $VISUAL and
            $GEM_EDITOR variables.

  Defaults:
    -e vi
